The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, July 27: Truckers today said 60 lakh trucks will go off the road across the country from August 6 in an indefinite strike to press for a relook of the toll policy and lower toll tax. We have decided to proceed on indefinite strike from August 6 opposing the present hefty toll charges levied on vehicles, which has become the death knell for the road transport industry, G.R. Shanmugappa, president of All India Motor Transport Congress, said.                             
	 New Delhi, July 27: The Coal India initial public offer is likely to hit the market by October, disinvestment secretary Sumit Bose said. The government expects to mop up about Rs 15,000 crore through this issue. Officials said the Coal India board was meeting on August 5 to finalise the draft red herring prospectus.                             
	 New Delhi, July 27: A formal bid to acquire BPs stake in an offshore Vietnamese gasfield will be jointly filed within weeks by ONGC and PetroVietnam, petroleum secretary S. Sundareshan has said. We met with the Prime Minister of Vietnam and we said we would work with PetroVietnam, he said.                             
	 New Delhi, July 27: SpiceJet has announced fresh orders for 30 Boeing 737-800 aircraft at a cost of $2.7 billion, deliveries of which will commence from 2014, company director Ajay Singh said.                            
	 Mumbai, July 27: Market regulator Sebi today suggested that a part of portfolio managers fee should be paid only if the client gained from the capital markets.                             
	 New Delhi, July 27: The government today told the Lok Sabha that 18 SEZs had been scrapped on the back of developers being impacted by the global economic slowdown.
                                                                                                                          
